flowRoot.flowPara: processing and indexing of research data on an open platform

text.tspan: Research requires data to continuously be processed, analyzed and visualized; data needs to be quality checked, verified and
backed up. Data and metadata need to be made publicly available in an easy to find and use manner. Many of these tasks can be
automated, which usually leads to fewer errors and a higher results quality. To facilitate these tasks, we introduce a suite of
microservices for the G-Node data infrastructure (GIN), an open platform for collaboration and sharing of research data and code.
